125	https://babyvc.substack.com/p/a-new-german-unicorn-metas-orion	A new German unicorn, Meta‚Äôs Orion glasses, the latest in AI, and much more...	What's Up Tech? #193	<html><head></head><body><p>Welcome to our <strong>193rd </strong>newsletter, written with üñ§ by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/annika-bautista-453106168/">Annika Bautista</a> and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarah-luna-mongin/">Sarah Luna Mongin</a></p><pre><code>üîç Topics we'll cover this week</code></pre><ul><li><p><strong>Fundraising &amp; general news from the week</strong>: a new unicorn joins the ranks in Germany, Meta unveils futuristic ‚ÄòOrion‚Äô glasses, and much more!</p></li><li><p><strong>Up-and-coming ventures to watch: </strong>UK startups‚Äô game coming out on top this week!</p></li><li><p><strong>Internships &amp; Job</strong> <strong>offers</strong> of the week </p></li></ul><p>Enjoy the read! üíõ</p><pre><code><code>ü§ë Fundraisings of the week</code></code></pre><h3>üèãÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Gymlib‚Äôs parent EGYM secures ‚Ç¨180 million to fast-track unicorn ambitions in Germany (üá©üá™)</h3><p><a href="https://egym.com/us">EGYM</a>, the German fitness technology and corporate wellness company, secured ‚Ç¨180 million in growth capital, propelling its valuation to over ‚Ç¨1 billion and solidifying its status as a unicorn. ü¶Ñ</p><p>The investment goal is to support EGYM's Wellpass corporate wellness network and facilitate further expansion. Additionally, the company aims to increase its market share in France through its subsidiary <a href="https://gymlib.com/en">Gymlib</a>, acquired in 2022. </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/09/24/egym-a-connected-fitness-startup-conceived-after-the-founder-hit-a-wall-at-the-gym-is-ramping-up-with-200m-at-a-1-2b-valuation/">EGYM, a Connected Fitness Startup Lands $200M at a $1.2B+ Valuation</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üöÉ Distribusion raises $80 million to expand its B2B ground transportation marketplace (üá©üá™)</h3><p><a href="https://www.distribusion.com/">Distribusion</a>, the B2B marketplace for ground transportation, has raised $80 million, led by <a href="https://www.tqventures.com/">TQ Ventures</a>, with participation from existing investor <a href="https://www.lightrock.com/">Lightrock</a>. The startup has created a platform <strong>that connects the biggest travel retailers</strong>, such as Booking.com, <strong>with the biggest carriers</strong>, such as SNCF. They are working on providing a holistic experience for travelers ‚Äî from bus to train to shuttle services ‚Äî all in one platform, with one contract. üìù</p><p>This Series C funding will be used for<strong> global expansion</strong> and <strong>additional technological investments</strong> to support thousands of customers and millions of travelers. üß≥ </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.finsmes.com/2024/09/distribusion-raises-80m-in-series-c-funding.html?_bhlid=a82c7308109f2e5cf8d3aa7c5140fce316e35192">Distribusion Raises $80M in Series C Funding</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>ü©∫ SURGAR lands ‚Ç¨11 million to innovate augmented reality in healthcare (<strong>üá´üá∑</strong>)</h3><p>French startup <a href="https://surgar-surgery.com/">SURGAR</a> has secured ‚Ç¨11 million in funding to advance its augmented reality (AR) solutions for minimally invasive surgery. This innovation promises to make surgeries safer, faster, and more precise, with the goal of <strong>reducing complications</strong> by 50% and <strong>increasing precision</strong> by 20 times. üîé</p><p>Patients benefit from fewer complications, reduced cancer recurrence, and shorter recovery times, while healthcare providers can expect significant cost savings due to improved surgical efficiency and shorter hospital stays.</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://tech.eu/2024/09/26/surgar-secures-eur11m-for-augmented-reality-surgical-solution/">SURGAR Secures ‚Ç¨11M for Augmented Reality Surgical Solution</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üß¨ Constructive Bio rounds up $58 million to advance synthetic genomics (üá¨üáß)</h3><p>The London-based startup, <a href="https://www.constructive.bio/">Constructive Bio</a>, has raised <strong>one of the largest biotech Series A rounds</strong> <strong>in the UK</strong> in recent years. The startup is working in the field of synthetic genomics with applications ranging from therapeutics to sustainable biomaterial creation. </p><p>According to its founder,  <a href="https://www.constructive.bio/blog/news/constructive-bio-secures-58-million-in-series-a-financing">Professor Jason Chin</a> <em>‚ÄúConstructive Bio is the only company that can turn living cells into sustainable biofactories in which they can program [‚Ä¶] proteins and new biopolymers.‚Äù</em><strong> </strong>üè≠ </p><p>This funding round will support further research and the commercialization of its breakthrough technologies.</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.uktech.news/biotech/synthetic-genomics-startup-constructive-bio-secures-43-4m-20240925">Synthetic Genomics Startup Constructive Bio Secures ¬£43.4m</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üî® All Iron Ventures rebrands to Acurio and closes ‚Ç¨150 million fund to invest in European startups (üá™üá∏)</h3><p>Spanish venture capital firm All Iron Ventures has rebranded as <a href="https://www.acurio.vc/">Acurio Ventures</a> and closed its third fund at ‚Ç¨150 million to focus exclusively on <strong>follow-on investments</strong>. </p><p>With a generalist approach, Acurio will invest across various sectors in Europe, targeting equity stakes between 3% and 10% to maintain flexibility in its follow-on investments and divestments. AV has already made around 20 investments from the new fund, further solidifying its presence in the European startup ecosystem. ü§ù</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/09/23/all-iron-ventures-rebrands-as-acurio-ventures-with-a-new-e150m-follow-on-fund/">All Iron Ventures Rebrands as Acurio Ventures With a New ‚Ç¨150M ‚ÄòFollow-On‚Äô Fund</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üî• Up-and-coming startups to watch</code></code></pre><h3><strong>üßë‚Äçü§ù‚Äçüßë </strong>UK-based startup Convergence creating personal AI agents just raised a Pre-Seed round (<strong>üá¨üáß)</strong></h3><p><a href="https://convergence.ai/">Convergence</a> received $12 million in Pre-Seed funding to develop advanced models powering their Proxy assistants, designed to automate repetitive tasks and workflows for human users.</p><p>Unlike many companies focusing on narrow AI agents for specific roles like sales or HR, Convergence aims to build a more <strong>flexible</strong>, general class of AI agents. Co-founder <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marvin-purtorab-511542234/">Purtorab</a> explained, ‚Äú<em>Our goal is to create agents that can <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/09/25/convergence-ai-played-with-agents-for-years-until-raising-12m-to-give-them-long-term-memory/">adapt to any type of task</a> based on user needs, reducing the need for numerous specialized tools.</em>‚Äù</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.balderton.com/news/convergence-raises-12m-to-build-personal-ai-agents-with-long-term-memory/">Convergence Raises $12M to Build Personal AI Agents with Long-Term Memory</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>ü¶æ Vsim is set to enhance robotics with simulation tech, raising $24 million in Seed funding (üá¨üáß)</h3><p><a href="https://v-sim.co.uk/">Vsim</a>, a robotics simulation engine founded by NVIDIA alums, has raised $24 million in Seed funding led by EQT Ventures. The company‚Äôs physics-based simulation technology is designed to help robots <strong>learn and operate in virtual environments</strong>. With this funding, they plan to expand their platform and cater to <strong>high-performance, real-time simulations</strong>. Their innovation couldn‚Äôt come at a better time with the nascence of AI, processing, and mechanics. üëå</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2024/09/25/vsim-founded-by-nvidia-alums-raises-21-5m-for-robotics-simulation-tech/">Vsim, Founded by Nvidia Alums, Raises $24 million for Robotics Tech Simulation</a></p></blockquote><pre><code>üì∞ News of the week</code></pre><h3>‚ö° Another Zuck flex, the Meta ‚ÄòOrion‚Äô AR glasses</h3><p>Meta officially unveiled its Orion augmented reality (AR) glasses, described as the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oX7OduG1YmI">company's most advanced AR prototype to date</a>. During the Meta Connect event, CEO Mark Zuckerberg emphasized that Orion represents a significant leap forward in AR technology, integrating features such as a lightweight design (weighing just 100 grams), Micro LED projectors, and a neural wristband for gesture control. üï∂Ô∏è</p><p>The device should provide users with immersive digital experiences by projecting holographic content directly into their field of vision, allowing for seamless interaction with both the physical and digital worlds. The Orion glasses are <strong>not yet available for public purchase</strong>, as they remain in the development phase. </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://about.fb.com/news/2024/09/introducing-orion-our-first-true-augmented-reality-glasses/">Introducing Orion, Our First True Augmented Reality Glasses</a></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h3>üëÄ OpenAI is looking to raise the biggest venture capital round of all time, amid forecasted losses and structural changes (üá∫üá∏)</h3><p>OpenAI is setting their eyes on raising $6.5 billion at a $150 billion pre-money valuation. So far, Thrive Capital has committed $1.25 billion, and investors are asked to provide <strong>at least $250 million in funding to participate</strong>. üí∞ To increase the attractiveness of the deal for investors, the company is also making plans to <a href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/openai-remove-non-profit-control-give-sam-altman-equity-sources-say-2024-09-25/">shift into a new structure ‚Äî from a non-profit to a for-profit company</a>. </p><p>In case you missed it, the New York Times published an article discussing the <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/27/technology/openai-chatgpt-investors-funding.html?smid=nytcore-android-share">financial state of Open AI,</a> highlighting that the company is expecting to lose $5 billion this year and special investment terms with Thrive Capital. </p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.axios.com/2024/09/20/openai-largest-vc-round?stream=top">OpenAI Closes In on Largest VC Round of All Time</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üëî Internships &amp; job offers</code></code></pre><h3>Internships</h3><p>Visiting Investment Analyst - <strong>Dealflow.eu </strong>(Lisbon)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://dealflow.eu/application-visiting-analyst/#:~:text=Visiting%20Investment%20Analyst">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Investment Team Intern - <strong>Grey Silo Ventures </strong>(Milan)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://cerealdocks.intervieweb.it/jobs/investment-team-intern-mf-grey-silo-ventures-46645/it/?utm_source=innovatorsroom&amp;utm_medium=innovatorsroom&amp;utm_campaign=innovatorsroom&amp;utm_content=innovatorsroom&amp;i12m_id=i12m-2024-9-HLM">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Growth Capital &amp; VC Intern - <strong>Astanor</strong> (Brussels)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/astanor_growth-capital-vc-investment-intern-ugcPost-7224349351043571712-kpJa/?utm_source=innovatorsroom&amp;utm_medium=innovatorsroom&amp;utm_campaign=innovatorsroom&amp;utm_content=innovatorsroom&amp;i12m_id=i12m-2024-7-FOO">‚û§&nbsp;Job  desc.</a></p></blockquote><p></p><h3>Jobs</h3><p>Investment Analyst / Associate - <strong>Katapult Ocean </strong>(Oslo)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://katapult.teamtailor.com/jobs/4998139-investment-analyst-associate?utm_source=venturecapitalcareers">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Investment Manager - <strong>Techstars</strong> (London)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://boards.greenhouse.io/techstars57/jobs/7633090002?utm_source=venturecapitalcareers">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><p>Operations Associate - <strong>Systemiq Capital</strong> (London)</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://apply.workable.com/kupa-global/j/07D2D3A10D/?">‚û§&nbsp;Job desc.</a></p></blockquote><pre><code><code>üôã‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Just before you leave...</code></code></pre><p>We hear you, and we‚Äôre planning a new <strong>deep dive‚Ä¶on AI</strong>!<strong> </strong>Answer the quick survey below to help us know if we‚Äôre on the right track ‚¨áÔ∏è</p><div class="poll-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;id&quot;:218911}" data-component-name="PollToDOM"></div><p></p><p>üëâ If you‚Äôd like to discover more internship &amp; job offers, you can check our LinkedIn Fridays‚Äô post <strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/babyvc_every-week-we-go-through-various-job-boards-activity-7245452214884872192-AV0b?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop">just here</a></strong>!</p><p>You can also read more about baby vc on <strong><a href="https://www.babyvc.co/">our website</a></strong> and follow our updates on <strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/30734593/">LinkedIn</a></strong>, or directly reach out to us at <strong>hello@baby-vc.co</strong>! ü§ù</p><h4></h4><p>The whole baby vc crew üñ§</p><p></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://babyvc.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://babyvc.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://babyvc.substack.com/p/a-new-german-unicorn-metas-orion/comments&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Leave a comment&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data