147	https://www.eu.vc/p/understanding-board-responsibilities	Understanding board responsibilities and governance	by Roberta Tihomirova, Head of Marketing at Eleven Ventures. | Originally published on Eleven Ventures.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/roberta-tihomirova-20694a186/">Roberta Tihomirova</a>, Head of Marketing at <a href="https://www.11.vc/">Eleven Ventures</a>. | Originally published on <a href="https://www.11.vc/understanding-board-responsibilities-and-governance/">Eleven Ventures</a>.</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png" width="1200" height="630" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:630,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:237967,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22452ce0-69da-4fe2-82ea-e8303bc1c1c1_1200x630.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Before diving into the intricacies of building a world-class board, let‚Äôs pause and ask: Why even have a board?</p><p>While it seems to be a given, especially for venture funded companies, few founders or board members truly consider the actual value a board can and should provide. The answer is very specific to the type of company, the founders, and the challenge that the business needs to overcome. One possible answer is that the board is the only place where founders can navigate the inherent complexity of building a startup. They do so by having an ongoing discussion with involved people that share incentives but are not fully immersed in the day-to-day operations. As humans, we create reality by sharing with others, hence the board is a way of creating reality. If this perspective seems too abstract, consider this: the board is the place where founders can work on the company instead of in the company. It‚Äôs an opportunity to take a step back and look at the bigger picture once a quarter, gaining a sense of accomplishment and future direction. And it is a Board Member‚Äôs opportunity to provide this perspective.</p><h3><strong>Fiduciary Duties: The Cornerstone of Effective Governance<br></strong></h3><p>At the heart of a board director‚Äôs role are fiduciary duties, which serve as the bedrock of trust and integrity within the boardroom. These duties are not just ethical guidelines ‚Äì they are legal obligations that require directors to prioritize the company‚Äôs interests above all else. Here we will get you familiar with the two most important fiduciary duties* ‚Äì the duty of Care and the duty of Loyalty.</p><p><em>*A fiduciary duty is the legal responsibility to act solely in the best interest of another party. ‚ÄúFiduciary‚Äù means trust, and a person with a fiduciary duty has a legal obligation to maintain that trust.</em></p><ol><li><p><strong>Duty of Care: Informed Decision-Making</strong></p></li></ol><ul><li><p>Directors must make well-informed decisions by thoroughly understanding all relevant information.</p></li><li><p>Reliance on expert advice is permitted, but it must be reasonable and made in good faith.</p></li><li><p>Active participation in board deliberations is required, with delegation limited to specific decision-making responsibilities.</p></li></ul><ol start="2"><li><p><strong>Duty of Loyalty: Prioritizing the Company‚Äôs Interests</strong></p></li></ol><ul><li><p>Directors must act in the company‚Äôs best interests, avoiding conflicts of interest and refraining from using their position for personal gain.</p></li><li><p>This duty underscores the importance of integrity and ethical behavior in board decisions.</p></li><li><p>The Duty of Loyalty also extends to safeguarding the company‚Äôs confidential information. Directors must ensure that sensitive data is not misused or disclosed inappropriately, as this could harm the company‚Äôs competitive position.</p></li></ul><p>Beyond these, directors are also bound by the duties of:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Obedience</strong> ‚Äì directors abide by all applicable laws and regulations.</p></li><li><p><strong>Confidentiality</strong> ‚Äì directors keep certain type of information confidential.</p></li><li><p><strong>Prudence</strong> ‚Äì be aware of risks and exercise caution when making decisions; approve expenditures wisely.</p></li><li><p><strong>Disclose</strong> ‚Äì if directors have information that would influence their decisions or impact the decisions of other board members, they have a duty to make that information known.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Navigating Conflicts of Interest: A Delicate Balance</strong></h3><p>Unfortunately, life is always messier. Although the above principles are universally accepted, most board directors serve different ‚Äúmasters‚Äù in their heads. VCs representatives prioritize their VC fund, co-founders might focus on their team or their customers, and so on. Many heated discussions and conflicts on boards arise because directors have different priorities, even though everyone assumes they are acting in the best long-term interests of the company.</p><p>To manage these conflicts effectively, directors must engage in open, honest communication. The board should establish clear guidelines for identifying and managing conflicts of interest, ensuring that all directors understand their responsibilities in this area. When conflicts arise, it‚Äôs important to address them head-on, fostering an environment where differing viewpoints can be discussed openly and resolved in a way that aligns with the company‚Äôs long-term goals.</p><h3><strong>The Role and Responsibilities of the Board: Governance in Action</strong></h3><p>The board‚Äôs role extends beyond mere oversight. While the board does not involve itself in day-to-day operations, it plays a crucial role in setting the strategic direction of the company. This responsibility is encapsulated in the principle of ‚ÄúNose in, hands out,‚Äù which suggests that while the board should be deeply informed about the company‚Äôs activities, it should refrain from micromanaging.</p><p>Key responsibilities of the board include:</p><ol><li><p><strong>Strategic Oversight</strong>: The board is responsible for guiding the company‚Äôs long-term strategy. This involves reviewing and approving major initiatives, such as market expansion, product development, and mergers or acquisitions. Directors should ensure that the company‚Äôs strategy is aligned with its mission and values and that it is adaptable to changing market conditions.<br></p></li><li><p><strong>CEO and Executive Management Oversight</strong>: One of the board‚Äôs most critical functions is the selection, evaluation, and, if necessary, replacement of the CEO. The board must also set appropriate compensation for the CEO and senior management, aligning incentives with the company‚Äôs performance and long-term goals. Regular performance reviews help ensure that the CEO and management team are executing the board‚Äôs strategic vision effectively.<br></p></li><li><p><strong>Risk Management</strong>:&nbsp;The board must oversee the company‚Äôs risk management framework, ensuring that all potential risks‚Äîfinancial, operational, legal, and reputational‚Äîare identified and mitigated. Directors should ensure that the company has adequate insurance, internal controls, and crisis management plans in place.</p></li><li><p><strong>Compliance and Ethical Oversight</strong>: Directors are responsible for ensuring that the company adheres to all relevant laws, regulations, and ethical standards. This includes setting policies on issues like environmental impact, social responsibility, and corporate governance.<br></p></li></ol><h3><strong>The Path to Effective Board Governance</strong></h3><p>Board governance is not just about ticking boxes; it‚Äôs about creating value for the company and its stakeholders. By understanding and embracing their fiduciary duties, board directors can build a foundation of trust, integrity, and strategic foresight that drives the company towards sustainable success. Effective governance requires a delicate balance of oversight and empowerment, where directors guide the company‚Äôs vision while enabling the management team to execute it.</p><p>As a board director, your role is to ensure that every decision contributes to the long-term prosperity of the company. By fostering transparency, managing conflicts of interest, and staying committed to your fiduciary duties, you can help steer the company through the complexities of growth and innovation, ensuring that it not only survives but thrives in a competitive landscape.</p><p>Coming up next ‚Äì strategic planning and execution oversight. </p><p>Stay tuned for Chapter 2!</p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" width="1100" height="220" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:220,&quot;width&quot;:1100,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:60754,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" cl