108	https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/p/fundraising-case-study-beehiiv	Fundraising Case Study: Beehiiv	How Tyler Denk Raised $50 million	<html><head></head><body><p>Hey y‚Äôall ‚Äî this week we launched the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@foundingjourney?sub_confirmation=1">Founding Journey Podcast</a>, and released episodes with <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hZunLjk_5QA">Tyler Denk from beehiiv</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uyYdcyFLURE">Steven Galanis from Cameo</a>.</p><p>But I also wrote up a case study on Tyler‚Äôs journey raising $50 million for beehiiv, where he goes deep on:</p><ul><li><p>What made their seed round so tough</p></li><li><p>The importance of getting leverage (especially with fundraising)</p></li><li><p>What to look for with angel investors</p></li></ul><p>And a lot more, below!</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h2><strong>Fundraising Case Study: beehiiv</strong></h2><p><a href="https://upgrade.foundingjourney.com">Become a member</a> to get full access to our case study library, private founder community, and more.</p><p>We can also help your startup in a few other ways:</p><h3><strong>Content Creation</strong></h3><p>Let my team and I <a href="https://s665g04yp0s.typeform.com/to/rOXjvxHU">ghostwrite</a> for your newsletter, X, or LinkedIn.</p><h3><strong>Growth</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/megaphone">Grow your audience + generate leads</a> with my growth service.</p><h3><strong>Fundraising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/fundraise">Share your round</a> with hundreds of investors in my personal network.</p><h3><strong>Advising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/advising">I‚Äôll help solve</a> a specific challenge you‚Äôre facing with your startup.</p><p>Advertise in my newsletter to <a href="https://go.houck.news/partner">get in front of 60,000+ founders</a>.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png" width="618" height="541.8279069767442" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:377,&quot;width&quot;:430,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:618,&quot;bytes&quot;:15742,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><h3><strong>Please briefly introduce yourself and your startup.</strong></h3><p>I‚Äôm <strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tyler-denk/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Tyler</a></strong>, CEO and co-founder of <strong><a href="https://beehiiv.com/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">beehiiv</a></strong>.&nbsp;</p><p>I was the second employee at <strong><a href="https://www.morningbrew.com/daily?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Morning Brew</a></strong> and built a lot of the product and the growth tools that led to the success of Morning Brew.</p><p>beehiiv is an all-in-one platform for newsletters. It‚Äôs a creator-friendly newsletter platform that makes it easy to design, write, send, promote, monetize, and track the ROI of your newsletter.</p><h3><strong>Please share what you can about the fundraising journey for the company so far.</strong></h3><p>When I was 27 and my co-founders were 24, we didn‚Äôt have much capital to fund the business ourselves.&nbsp;</p><p>We raised a seed round of $2.6M. About 8 months later we achieved what I considered product-market fit and were around $15-20k in monthly revenue.</p><p>We raised a $1.6M seed extension to cover expenses, but eventually needed more.</p><p>By mid-2020, we raised a Series A of $12.5M from <strong><a href="https://lsvp.com/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Lightspeed</a></strong>.&nbsp;</p><p>At that point, our team was burnt out, and I was handling support tickets at midnight.&nbsp;</p><p>We had strong growth but I realized it wasn‚Äôt sustainable.&nbsp;</p><p>I drafted a plan envisioning what we‚Äôd do with $10M, and it became clear that raising more capital was necessary to ensure stability and mitigate risks, such as maintaining consistent growth and avoiding potential outages.</p><p>We eventually raised a $33M Series B from <strong><a href="https://www.nea.com/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">NEA</a></strong> and other investors to continue scaling.&nbsp;</p><p>Given the competitive market, the choice was between staying lean or going all-in to capture more market share.&nbsp;</p><p>I opted for the latter, understanding the risks, but also the potential for significant growth.</p><h2><strong>Fundraising Strategy</strong></h2><h3><strong>What did you plan ahead of time to use the money for?</strong></h3><p>We needed upfront contracts for services like Heroku and AWS, but we weren‚Äôt in a financial position to cover those costs. That‚Äôs actually a big part of why we did the seed round.</p><p>I made a classic founder mistake of thinking that a seed round of $2.6M was a large amount, especially with only 2 co-founders and minimal expenses.&nbsp;</p><p>But to be competitive, we had to offer benefits like 401(k)s and health insurance.&nbsp;</p><p>Top engineers cost over $200k and our runway quickly shortened. That‚Äôs when we raised our seed extension.</p><h2><strong>Investor Strategy</strong></h2><h3><strong>How did you decide which investors would be a good fit?</strong></h3><p>We looked for angel investors who could also be early adopters. For example, Houck invested.</p><p>When entering a very competitive market, I was fully aware that we had the least polished product on the market by nature, being a few weeks old.</p><p>But when we raised our seed round we actually raised from different strategic angels who had a newsletter on a competing platform.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>A very simple ask in the early days to build momentum was to have those angel investors move their newsletter over to beehiiv.&nbsp;</p><p>One of those angels was using another competitor and had 100k subscribers at the time.</p><p>I didn't even know that we could handle 100k emails being sent at once, but they moved over without hesitation and gave us a ton of credibility.</p><h2><strong>Fundraising Process</strong></h2><h3><strong>What did you emphasize in your pitch?</strong></h3><p>My 2 co-founders and I were also software engineers at Morning Brew.&nbsp;</p><p>In the early days, when the product wasn't up to snuff with the competition, we were selling a vision that we already did this, and that we‚Äôd built this at Morning Brew.</p><p>We said we're building the same tools but better. And maybe it wasn‚Äôt all built out at the time,&nbsp;but if you follow the success of Morning Brew, you're selling a narrative and the vision of what's to come.</p><p>I‚Äôd also pitched the ad network knowing that we were never going to write a single line of code for the ad network for probably a year and a half to two years.</p><p>We were building different dashboards and queries and structured our database around data that would eventually be used for optimizing ads at some point in the future. We showed we had a long-term plan.</p><p>The legacy platforms that have been around for 10 or 15 years would have to work through so much tech debt to retrofit their platform to be hyper optimized for ads.</p><p>It‚Äôs a massive bet. There aren‚Äôt that many super large ad networks and it hasn‚Äôt been done well in email anywhere.</p><h3><strong>What did you do to drive urgency among investors and close the round?</strong></h3><p>By building in public and openly sharing our growth metrics we create a narrative that everyone is moving to beehiiv, which reassures potential customers and builds credibility.</p><p>It also attracts investor interest. Whenever we hit milestones like $100k or $500k MRR, I receive numerous inquiries from investors wanting to lead future rounds.&nbsp;</p><p>I don‚Äôt waste time nurturing every potential investor relationship. Instead I focus on building the product. If our growth metrics are strong, investors will find us.</p><p>We raised our Series A in 7 days and Series B in 10, thanks to this approach.&nbsp;</p><p>I include potential investors in our monthly updates, which detail everything from what went well to our strategies and upcoming launches.&nbsp;</p><p>By the time we‚Äôre ready to raise funds, these investors are already well-informed and ready to engage, making the fundraising process much more effective and efficient.</p><h3><strong>What was the biggest challenge that came up during fundraising?</strong></h3><p>For the seed round it was tough.&nbsp;</p><p>Substack was venture-backed. They started 3 years before us. Their Series B had a $650M valuation.</p><p>Substack already had a multi year lead with probably at that point $80-90M of funding already secured.</p><p>Mailchimp's massive, they've exited and have multi billion dollars in revenue.&nbsp;</p><p>You could list two dozen other email providers and then at the exact time that we went out in the market, Twitter had just acquired Revue and Facebook just launched Bulletin.</p><p>It was established legacy players along with a new wave of VC-backed players that already had head starts on us.</p><h3><strong>Any unique or interesting fundraising stories you haven‚Äôt mentioned yet?</strong></h3><p><strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ffatemi21/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Faraz</a></strong> from Lightspeed had reached out to me on Twitter, LinkedIn, and email countless times, but I ignored all of them. I didn‚Äôt even read the emails; I just marked them as done.&nbsp;</p><p>Then they got creative. For any VCs, here‚Äôs a tip: they invited me to a founder's dinner in LA. At the time we were a remote company and I was spending 14 hours a day working alone.&nbsp;</p><p>I thought, ‚Äúyou know what? Meeting some other founders in LA sounds nice.‚Äù</p><p>After I agreed to attend, they suggested meeting for coffee first. I realized I‚Äôd been tricked, but I decided to go along with it since I was already planning to go to the dinner.&nbsp;</p><p>The call went well, and I did my usual thing ‚Äî I added them to our investor update list.&nbsp;</p><p>I didn‚Äôt want to keep giving them personalized updates, so I told them they‚Äôd get the same monthly update everyone else received, which would provide more detail than any 30-minute call could.</p><p>They stayed on that update list for 3 to 4 months. When I decided to raise a Series A, Lightspeed was on my shortlist since they had already shown a lot of interest.&nbsp;</p><p>I sent them an email, and because they had 4 months of context from those updates, they were ready to commit immediately. We had a term sheet within 4 to 5 days.</p><h2><strong>Reflection</strong></h2><h3><strong>What‚Äôs one piece of fundraising advice you‚Äôd give other founders?</strong></h3><p>Having leverage is so important as a founder.</p><p>Our Series A was the closest to ‚Äúneeding‚Äù to raise we‚Äôve dealt with yet.</p><p>There was a perfectly fine path forward of cutting our marketing spend and stretching it out until we turned it around or had better revenue before we ramped up.</p><p>For our Series B, we had over $10M in the bank and when we got our term sheet I said this isn't even close to what we're looking for and I have 0 urgency to take any deal in this situation.</p><p>We had $10M in the bank. We were totally good.&nbsp;</p><p>I knew the fork in the road where we could have accelerated and I did prefer that route.</p><p>That‚Äôs why we eventually got the terms that we liked and took a deal. But having leverage is the name of the game as a founder.</p><h3><strong>Who‚Äôs an investor you‚Äôd recommend other founders work with?</strong></h3><p><strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sasha-kaletsky-48a10378/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Sasha</a></strong> from <strong><a href="https://www.creator.ventures/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Creator Ventures</a></strong>. He participated in our seed, and when the market turned during our seed extension round, no one was investing.</p><p>Sasha stuck his neck out and told me he‚Äôd put together our seed extension round. He got his LPs involved and led the charge there.</p><p>Also, when we were hiring a VP of Finance, I had not hired one of these before, and Sasha inserted himself into our hiring process and told me to send him all the resumes and ran the interview process himself.</p><p>He‚Äôs punched well above his weight, Sasha is a legend.</p><h3><strong>Are there any resources you‚Äôd recommend to other founders?</strong></h3><p><strong><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Thinking-Fast-Slow-Daniel-Kahneman/dp/0374533555?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Thinking Fast and Slow</a></strong>. It‚Äôs more of a psychology book, but I think everything in the world comes down to understanding human psychology.&nbsp;</p><p>As a founder, having a good understanding of how to leverage that to your advantage is super powerful.</p><p>Also, sign up for <strong><a href="https://www.bigdeskenergy.com/?utm_source=foundingjourney.com&amp;utm_medium=referral">Big Desk Energy</a></strong>, my newsletter!&nbsp;</p><p>Lastly sending investor updates is so powerful (even before you have investors).</p><p>There are so many things happening at once. For me, the investor update is the way to get all my thoughts on paper.</p><p>Forcing yourself to be accountable and write that every month is both extremely clarifying for you and the team, but it‚Äôs also an opportunity to show investors how you think about the business.&nbsp;</p><p>This will do so much more than a pitch deck can do.</p><h3><strong>Do you have any hot takes regarding the fundraising process?</strong></h3><p>I think there are so many fallacies that companies use as accepted truths that I don't think are real.&nbsp;</p><p>They‚Äôll say things like, now that we are 80 people, we need to hire that VP, and then we need to implement a process and now we need to add this new process that didn't exist before.</p><p>There's a lot of accepted things that companies think they should do as they get larger.</p><p>One of those is that we have $40M in the bank so any problem that we have we can be solved by hiring someone to tackle that problem. I reject that.</p><p>I'm on the other end of the spectrum which is maybe too extreme. I prefer no managers and just having a flat org where everyone knows what they're responsible for.</p><p>I don't want to fall into the trap of having money, and thinking that we can do things that larger companies do. I want to continue to ship and operate as if we're a 5 person startup.</p><div><hr></div><h2><strong>How We Can Help</strong></h2><h3><strong>Content Creation</strong></h3><p>Let my team and I <a href="https://s665g04yp0s.typeform.com/to/rOXjvxHU">ghostwrite</a> for your newsletter, X, or LinkedIn.</p><h3><strong>Growth</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/megaphone">Grow your audience + generate leads</a> with my growth service.</p><h3><strong>Fundraising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/fundraise">Share your round</a> with hundreds of investors in my personal network.</p><h3><strong>Advising</strong></h3><p><a href="https://go.houck.news/advising">I‚Äôll help solve</a> a specific challenge you‚Äôre facing with your startup.</p><p>Advertise in my newsletter to <a href="https://go.houck.news/partner">get in front of 60,000+ founders</a>.</p></body></html>	The founder of beehiiv, Tyler Denk, shares his fundraising journey, emphasizing the importance of leverage and investor strategy.	2024-10-12 14:50:50	2024-10-14 07:37:25.244	2024-10-14 09:30:45.381	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4af84051-30dc-4b81-8de1-df0cfa71b7c8_430x377.png	Michael Houck	fundraising-case-study-beehiiv
107	https://www.theconsumervc.com/p/the-consumer-vc-roundup-89	The Consumer VC Roundup #89	This issue is brought to you by Propeller Industries.	<html><head></head><body><h4>This issue is brought to you by <a href="https://www.propellerindustries.com/">Propeller Industries</a>.</h4><p><strong>Propeller Industries</strong> is the leading strategic finance and accounting partner for venture-stage companies. Thinking about profitability, extending your runway, and improving efficiency in your operations? Propeller‚Äôs fractional model offers a dynamic solution that provides a cost-effective alternative to hiring full-time finance talent.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://www.propellerindustries.com/industries/cpg/" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png" width="280" height="105" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:300,&quot;width&quot;:800,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:280,&quot;bytes&quot;:104173,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://www.propellerindustries.com/industries/cpg/&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fff4f7a6f-fd96-4d0f-bbb1-f5e9322a2570_800x300.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.propellerindustries.com/industries/cpg/&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Click Here To Learn More&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://www.propellerindustries.com/industries/cpg/"><span>Click Here To Learn More</span></a></p><div><hr></div><p>Hey friends,</p><p>Hope you had a great week. The big news in CPG from this past week was BetterBrand, which produces high protein bagels and once valued at $176 million, seems to be in trouble. They delivered moldy products, unfulfilled many orders to customers and a few rumors ranging fromtheir founder/CEO is hiding out in Europe, to they‚Äôre shutting down or going through a hostile takeover. <a href="https://www.snaxshot.com/p/is-better-brand-shutting-down-company">Snaxshot has the story.</a></p><p>Last year, BetterBrand raised a $6 million Series A at a pre-money valuation of $170 million. What I didn‚Äôt understand at the time was why at that valuation you‚Äôre only raising $6 million. That‚Äôs only diluting less than 3.5% of the company. For a Series A, that‚Äôs a VERY small percentage. The commentary was focused on the pre-valuation number (which was BIG), not the amount raised number. After I read it last year, I texted an investor friend and told him I was puzzled and didn‚Äôt get it. He didn‚Äôt quite understand it either and thought of some situations. But the situations didn‚Äôt sound like normal situations. If anyone has reasons why this would happen in any deal (only dilute less than 3.5% of the business in the Series A), I‚Äôd love to hear them.</p><p>On to the consumer news of the week &amp; events for this month.</p><h2>This Week In Consumer</h2><h2>üßÉConsumer Brandsüëö</h2><h4>üí∞Fundraisesüí∞</h4><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.sofiepavittface.com/?srsltid=AfmBOopBRH_Tu_3qdb9wfC6w1MDoY7_gZt8x2Cyo9CWx9t16m7TsOvlq">Sofie Pavitt Face</a>, the skin-care brand founded by aesthetician Sofie Pavitt, has secured seed funding from True Beauty Ventures. Known as the "cool girl‚Äôs acne whisperer" by Nylon, Pavitt now has a notable investor backing her brand. <a href="https://www.beautyindependent.com/true-beauty-ventures-invests-sofie-pavitt-face/">BeautyIndependent</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www1.mhusa.com/">Mo√´t Hennessy</a> (LVMH Mo√´t Hennessy Louis Vuitton SE) has made a minority investment in <a href="https://www.frenchbloom.com/en?srsltid=AfmBOopqlx1rdlIDIW_IM5l3Lnd6WZlgxOGRB7Bj9wgLBLMiai7VdfL2">French Bloom</a>, a luxury nonalcoholic sparkling wine brand. French Bloom combines French chardonnay and pinot noir blends to meet the rising demand for alcohol moderation. This move follows Mo√´t Hennessy's reported decline in sparkling wine revenue during the first half of 2024. Financial details of the deal were not disclosed. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/moet-hennessy-invests-in-french-bloom-nonalcohol/729056/">FoodDive</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.meatable.com/">Meatable</a>, the Dutch cultivated meat startup, is preparing for its Series C funding round, scheduled for early 2025. The invite-only event will include investors, policymakers, and industry leaders. The funds raised will support the company's efforts to scale and commercialize its technology, with the ultimate goal of licensing its manufacturing capabilities to meat companies. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/meatable-preps-series-c-funding-round-hires-new-cto/728994/">FoodDive</a></p></li></ul><h4>üí∏M&amp;Aüí∏</h4><ul><li><p>Private equity firm <a href="https://www.bfly.com/">Butterfly Equity</a> is acquiring Duckhorn Portfolio, a luxury wine company, for $1.95 billion in an all-cash deal. Duckhorn, based in Napa Valley with 11 wineries across the West Coast, will become privately held but continue to operate under its name. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/butterfly-equity-duckhorn-portfolio-wine-purchase-acquisition-2-billion-napa-private/729092/">FoodDive</a></p></li><li><p>Mondelƒìz‚Äôs VC arm, <a href="https://www.snackfutures.com/">SnackFutures</a>, has acquired a minority stake in U.K. doughnut brand Urban Legend, known for its air-fried, lower-calorie treats. This move supports Mondelƒìz‚Äôs growth in the healthier bakery sector. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/mondelez-venture-capital-arm-buys-minority-stake-in-healthier-doughnut/728560/">FoodDive</a></p></li><li><p><a href="http://group.emmi.com/che/en">Emmi Group</a>, the Swiss milk processor and dairy products company, has finalized its acquisition of French pastry maker Mademoiselle Desserts Group. This move will create a "Desserts PowerHouse," doubling Emmi's sales in the premium desserts niche and positioning the company as a global leader in the growing premium dessert category. <a href="https://www.foodbusinessnews.net/articles/26977-emmi-acquires-mademoiselle-desserts">FoodBusinessNews</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.tengramcapital.com/">Tengram Capital Partners </a>has sold HRB Brands to Sodalis Group, a European beauty and personal care platform. HRB, known for brands like Alberto VO5, Zest, and Brut, is present in over 30 million households across the Americas. Under Tengram's ownership since 2020, HRB expanded into Latin America and strengthened its brand portfolio. <a href="https://www.gcimagazine.com/brands-products/news/news/22922518/sodalis-group-acquires-hrb-brands">GCIMagazine</a></p></li></ul><h4>üöÄDebuts, Distribution &amp; ExpansionüöÄ</h4><ul><li><p><a href="https://bumpinblends.com/?srsltid=AfmBOoqQvu8AWC6KsLtVWGZl7MWD7LGFzdJNBDrqyw4fX90A9OLuPOpp">Bumpin Blends</a>, founded by Lisa Mastela, MPH, RD, has launched its smoothie cubes at over 1,400 Walmart locations. The brand, known for simplifying nutrient intake, offers flavors like Watermelon Prickly Pear and Peanut Butter Cup. This expansion follows a successful launch in Sprouts and reflects its rapid growth, gaining celebrity fans like Jenna Dewan. PressRelease</p></li><li><p>Nestl√© is entering the global cuisine market, valued at $110 billion, by launching two new frozen brands: Mings for Asian food and Tapat√≠o for Mexican cuisine. Targeting younger consumers eager for bold, international flavors, Nestl√© partnered with celebrity chef Ming Tsai for Mings and collaborated with the family-owned Tapat√≠o hot sauce brand and Mexican chefs to ensure authentic taste. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/nestle-global-cuisine-mexican-asian-brands-frozen/729244/">FoodDive</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.chobani.com/">Chobani</a>, the strained yogurt brand, is expanding its high-protein offerings with a new line of Greek yogurt cups and drinks, featuring up to 30 grams of protein per serving. These products are made with natural ingredients and contain no added sugar, catering to the growing demand for nutrient-rich foods. The new line also includes a rebranded version of its former Complete drink, now part of the Chobani High Protein range. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/chobani-expands-presence-high-protein-greek-yogurt-launch/728722/">FoodDive</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://impossiblefoods.com/">Impossible Foods</a> is expanding its product lineup with three new family-friendly items: Lion King Chicken Nuggets (in collaboration with Disney), Meal Makers, and Impossible Corn Dogs. These ready-to-make products will be available in grocery stores in the coming weeks, aiming to appeal to a broader audience of plant-based food enthusiasts. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/impossible-foods-launches-three-new-accessible-products/729171/">FoodDive</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.uniqlo.com/us/en/?srsltid=AfmBOoqjAxcwazmnKe61YaILvrDWoywDjf06_7SUVYGUyfsYn9p2r-bx">Uniqlo </a>has reopened its expanded flagship store at White City's Westfield, now spanning two floors with a new Kids &amp; Baby section featuring a play area. Alongside the reopening, Uniqlo launched a Crisis x Mr Men Little Miss collaboration, supporting the homelessness charity by donating clothing to Crisis Christmas services. <a href="https://ww.fashionnetwork.com/news/Bigger-uniqlo-reopens-at-white-city-westfield-launches-kid-s-collab-with-homeless-charity-crisis,1670996.html">FashionNetwork</a></p></li><li><p>Parisian label <a href="https://www.soeur.fr/en">Soeur </a>has launched its first menswear line, Fr√®re. The brand describes the new collection as embodying polished, classic style with effortless elegance. Fr√®re aims to make getting dressed a cultural statement, reflecting personal influences like films, music, and books. Each piece is designed to tell a story, blending nonchalant ease with refined details. <a href="https://ww.fashionnetwork.com/news/Soeur-launches-into-menswear-with-frere-debut,1670410.html">FashionNetwork</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.deinde.com/?srsltid=AfmBOop4dZRHJeRUlpEk1jlrwt1nlaD8E4UPORhnIN9H7jmcLOxtXBVq">Deinde</a>, a clean clinical line targeting inflammation as part of a preventative skin health care regimen, launhches its Barrier-Building Moisture Cream, designed to aid in reducing the impacts of inflammaging to help sustain positive skin health and longevity. The face cream moisturizes and helps improve barrier function, and provides long-lasting moisture for soft, nourished skin. <a href="https://www.gcimagazine.com/brands-products/skin-care/news/22922270/deinde-introduces-skin-barrierbuilding-moisture-cream-to-tackle-inflammaging">GCIMagazine</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/rothea.official/">Rothea</a>, a new gentle and anti-aging skincare brand, will launch on November 1, inspired by a daughter's love for her mom with the tagline ‚ÄúBorn from love, made for you.‚Äù The debut product, Resilience Cream, features six scientifically proven ingredients, including 1% Bakuchiol, Vegan Phyto Collagen, a 4 Peptide Complex, Niacinamide, a 5 Ceramide complex, and Hyaluronic Acid, all packaged in FSC-certified materials. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-10/introducing-rothea-skincare-brand/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.elfcosmetics.com/?srsltid=AfmBOopdcVkBUn4zeim8ucQ5Aftr4fSgefWO5J2MgqwTZOZGZD5KPx9P">E.l.f. Cosmetics</a> has made its debut at Sephora Mexico, marking the brand‚Äôs first appearance in Sephora globally. This launch includes the brand‚Äôs viral ‚ÄúHoly Grails‚Äù and aims to democratize access to quality beauty products at affordable prices, empowering customers to express their true selves. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-10/elf-cosmetics-launches-at-sephora-mexico/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.meritbeauty.com/?srsltid=AfmBOorGe2F2T23L0OrPhkxkjzLAucNZ2-fDe0gZoJ9n6ej0oSKPJbpP">Merit</a>, the cruelty-free minimalist makeup brand, is making its first foray into fragrance with the launch of Retrospect, a complex scent developed over two years. This extrait de parfum features nearly 30% fragrance oil, ensuring long-lasting wear with just one spray. Retrospect will be available starting October 22nd, expanding Merit's minimalist beauty offerings into the fragrance category. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-09/merit-debuts-its-first-fragrance/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.cosrx.com/?srsltid=AfmBOoobB3xZ12C36A526CTyMs00Pk5-9RHxB-OrTCkJFoHRPmPOUTSK">Cosrx </a>has launched the Alpha-Arbutin 2 Skin Discoloration Serum, suitable for all skin types. This gentle serum targets blemish concerns, promoting a clearer complexion while soothing and hydrating irritated skin. The fast-absorbing formula enhances spot improvement and offers a refreshing, non-sticky feel. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-07/cosrx-debuts-alpha-arbutin-2-skin-discoloration-serum/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.sharkclean.com/page/hair-stylers?srsltid=AfmBOopcbddAmPuJTVLAQAhT6uwRqKbjg9lndTSkn6z5NU5YqENeAw2I">Shark Beauty</a> has launched two new Air Multi-Styling Systems, the Shark FlexFusion and Shark FlexFusion Straight. These ceramic tools feature air-straightening FlexFusion technology for damage-free heating, allowing for versatile styling on both wet and dry hair. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-03/shark-beauty-launches-two-new-air-multi-styling-systems/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li></ul><h4>ü™áCollabsü™á</h4><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.nexxus.com/">Nexxus </a>has launched "The Style Swap" collab with Lindsay Lohan, highlighting the versatility of its Styling Line. The campaign recreates iconic looks from Lohan's fan-favorite characters, showing off the range of styles achievable with Nexxus products. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-10/nexxus-launches-the-style-swap-campaign-with-lindsay-lohan/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.thglabs.com/">THG Labs</a> has partnered with Clean Food Group to develop sustainable raw materials and oils for beauty and personal care products using food waste. This collaboration aims to create low-impact, high-performance oils, drawing on THG's extensive experience in skincare, haircare, and suncare. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-09/thg-labs-partners-with-clean-food-group-for-more-sustainability-in-cosmetics/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.wella.com/professional/en-EN/home">Wella Professionals </a>has launched a new Power Duo inspired by the upcoming movie musical <em>Wicked</em>, marking its first global co-branded partnership. The limited-edition Ultimate Repair and Color collections feature movie-themed packaging and include formulas designed to repair and strengthen both hair and nails. This collaboration ties into the story of Elphaba and Glinda, highlighting their unique friendship and destinies. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-08/wella-debuts-wicked-inspired-power-duo/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.sallyhansen.com/en-us">Sally Hansen</a> has launched a limited-edition Halloween collection in collaboration with Reese‚Äôs. The Sally Hansen x Reese‚Äôs collection includes eight Insta-Dri nail polishes, two glow-in-the-dark shades, and two Salon Effects Perfect Manicure designs, all themed for the spooky season. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-04/sally-hansen-launches-reeses-collection-for-halloween/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.galderma.com/">Galderma </a>has extended its decade-long partnership with the National Breast Cancer Foundation (NBCF) to continue supporting breast cancer research and treatment efforts. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-02/galderma-continues-partnership-with-brest-cancer-foundation/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li></ul><h4>‚Ü™Ô∏èRebrands &amp; Relaunches‚Ü©Ô∏è</h4><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.sunshinebotanicals.com/">Sunshine Botanicals</a> has rebranded with new earth-tone packaging that highlights its holistic skincare approach. The updated look reflects a commitment to authenticity and wellness, while the product line remains unchanged, focusing on rejuvenating and restoring aging and problematic skin using natural elements. <a href="https://www.beautypackaging.com/contents/view_breaking-news/2024-10-07/sunshine-botanicals-rebrands-with-new-packaging/?widget=listSection">BeautyPackaging</a></p></li></ul><h4>üîªClosuresüîª</h4><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.lambweston.com/">Lamb Weston</a>, the supplier of frozen potato products, plans to close its aging processing plant in Connell, Washington, and temporarily cut certain production lines across North America. This restructuring includes a 4% workforce reduction, affecting about 428 jobs. CEO Tom Werner cited sluggish demand as the reason, expecting it to continue through fiscal 2025. <a href="https://www.fooddive.com/news/french-fry-maker-lamb-weston-close-plant-cut-jobs/728624/">FoodDive</a></p></li></ul><h2>üíªConsumer Softwareüíª</h2><h4>üí∞Fundraisesüí∞</h4><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.farther.com/">Farther</a>, the leading technology-centric financial advisory firm, closed a $72 million Series C funding round to expand its advisor network and enhance its wealth management platform. Co-led by CapitalG, the independent growth fund of Alphabet (Google's parent company), and Viewpoint Ventures, this funding&nbsp;round elevates Farther's post-money valuation to $542&nbsp;million. <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/farther-secures-72-million-series-c-from-capitalg-and-viewpoint-ventures-to-continue-revolutionizing-wealth-management-302273094.html">PRNewsWire</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://holobiome.org/">Holobiome </a>has closed an oversubscribed Seed round of $9M. The round was led by iSelect Fund, with major participation from Corundum Systems Biology, Satori Neuro, SkyRiver Ventures, Pace Ventures, Valor Equity Partners, and Astanor. The company's initial success with substantial non-dilutive funding laid the groundwork for this sizeable institutional round.&nbsp; <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/holobiome-a-microbiome-platform-startup-targeting-the-gut-brain-axis-closes-oversubscribed-seed-round-302270737.html">PRNewsWire</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://opengradient.ai/">OpenGradient</a>, a leading decentralized AI infrastructure company, has raised $8.5M in seed funding. With a mission to accelerate open-source AI, OpenGradient democratizes model ownership, streamlines AI deployment, and enables universal access to AI. <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/opengradient-raises-8-5m-to-decentralize-ai-infrastructure-and-accelerate-secure-open-source-ai-302270745.html">PRNewsWire</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://mewe.com/">MeWe</a>, a privacy-focused social media network with over 20 million users, is launching a growth agenda to promote Web3. The Series B funding round, led by McCourt Global, aims to accelerate MeWe's growth and drive innovation. Plans include AI integration, new Web3 features, targeted user acquisition marketing, and the introduction of a native token to boost user engagement and platform utility. <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mewe-secures-initial-6-million-series-b-investment-to-further-integrate-web3-for-platforms-20-million-users-302271741.html">PRNewsWire</a></p></li></ul><h3>üõíeCommerce &amp; Retail Techüõí</h3><h4>üí∞Fundraisesüí∞</h4><ul><li><p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/flexfactor">FlexFactor</a>, a cutting-edge provider of decline recovery solutions for eCommerce brands, announced the completion of its $16.8 Series A funding round. The round was led by Bessemer Venture Partners, with additional participation from seed investors. <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/flexfactor-raises-16-8m-series-a-from-bessemer-venture-partners-to-tackle-the-500-billion-ecommerce-problem-checkout-failures-due-to-payment-declines-302273131.html">PRNewsWire</a></p></li><li><p><a href="https://www.numeric.io/">Numeric </a>has raised a $28 million Series A round led by Menlo Ventures,&nbsp;with participation from new investors IVP and Socii Capital, and existing investors Founders Fund, 8VC, Long Journey, Access Industries, and Friends &amp; Family Capital, and others. This investment will accelerate engineering hiring and product development, supporting Numeric's aim to enable real-time decision-making from financial data. <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/28m-series-a-fuels-numerics-mission-to-build-the-next-gen-financial-data-platform-302273249.html">PRNewsWire</a></p></li></ul><div><hr></div><h4><strong><a href="https://lu.ma/uclb42k3">Atlanta, GA ‚Üí üçπ Atlanta Consumer with Phreshly &amp;