substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png" width="1456" height="740" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:740,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:634482,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://www.deckmatch.com/&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Connect your top-of-funnel to Deckmatch and <em>transform pitch decks and URLs into structured and insightful data</em>. Get detailed firmographic and people data, in-depth competitive and market analysis, and personalized investment memo without lifting a finger. The&nbsp;cherry on the cake? It's all seamlessly synced to your preferred tools like Affinity through our API integrations.</p><p>Never miss a deal, ditch the donkey work, and build meaningful relationships faster.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.deckmatch.com/&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Try Deckmatch&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:&quot;button-wrapper&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary button-wrapper" href="https://www.deckmatch.com/"><span>Try Deckmatch</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h2>Time Between Funding Rounds: Magic Number 18</h2><p>Carta‚Äôs latest <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/peterjameswalker_startups-fundraising-venturecapital-activity-7249829848725004288-RPF_?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop">analysis</a> of funding rounds reveals that startups follow diverse paths when raising funds, with some moving swiftly through the rounds, while others take years to secure capital. Though fast growth is often celebrated, long-term success isn‚Äôt always tied to speed, and slower-moving startups may be laying the groundwork for future triumphs.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Seed round movers:</strong> In 2024, 32% of startups raising a priced seed round were founded in 2023, but some date back to 2017.  </p></li><li><p><strong>Series B spread:</strong> 16% of Series B fundraisers were from 2019 startups, while 4% came from companies founded in 2023.  </p></li><li><p><strong>Older Series D rounds:</strong> 18% of Series D fundraisers this year trace back to 2016, showing how the venture landscape supports long-term growth.  </p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg" width="688" height="688" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:800,&quot;width&quot;:800,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:688,&quot;bytes&quot;:90838,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa73022d8-027a-4b37-913e-64b6054d444b_800x800.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><blockquote><h4><em><strong>‚úàÔ∏è KEY TAKEAWAYS</strong></em></h4><p><em>Startup success isn‚Äôt always a sprint. Some companies need time to mature, and although quick funding boosts valuations, slower paths can lead to sustained success too. In short, the median is 1y from incorporation to Seed, 3y to Series A, 4.5y to Series B, and 6y to Series C. Said differently, <strong>one round every 18 months seems to be the rule of thumb.</strong></em></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h2>Predicting Success for Seed Startups</h2><p>An <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/adamshuaib_we-analyzed-the-profiles-of-every-seed-startup-activity-7249342645687259136-WDIr?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop">analysis</a> by Adam Shuaib of every seed startup in Europe since 2010 reveals valuable insights about success predictors.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Top talent matters:</strong> The ability to hire top talent post-raise is one of the strongest success indicators.  </p></li><li><p><strong>Experience isn‚Äôt key:</strong> Founders with less than five years of experience were just as likely to raise funds as those with 15+ years.  </p></li><li><p><strong>Speed counts:</strong> Startups raising a seed round within one year of incorporation were more than twice as likely to reach Series A/B compared to those that took four or more years.</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png" width="1456" height="866" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:866,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:205827,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb549bdc2-590c-4a71-8838-97d9d4a2f37b_2010x1196.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">While industry expertise is not the single most deciding factor overall, it correlates somewhat with the founders‚Äô ability to generate revenue, according to Hasai &amp; Zaker (<a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/sej.1406">2021</a>) </figcaption></figure></div><blockquote><h4><em><strong>‚úàÔ∏è KEY TAKEAWAYS</strong></em></h4><p><em>Speed and the ability to hire top talent outshine experience and educational background. Fast action and strong teams seem to be the real predictors of long-term startup success.</em></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><div><hr></div><h2>The New Normal for SaaS Growth in 2024  </h2><p>According to the latest SaaS Retention <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/sofia-simarro-faustino_saas-data-metrics-activity-7236725911386025984--qag?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop">Report</a> by ChartMogul, SaaS companies are entering a new era of slower, sustainable growth. While expansion remains important, net revenue retention (NRR) is becoming increasingly difficult to maintain at 100%, especially for companies with larger subscriber bases.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Expansion-driven growth:</strong> For companies with $15M‚Äì30M ARR, expansion contributes 40% to growth, up from 30% in 2021.  </p></li><li><p><strong>NRR struggles:</strong> Only 6% of companies with over 12K subscribers hit 100% NRR, compared to 23% with smaller subscriber counts.  </p></li><li><p><strong>Subscriber impact:</strong> Companies with fewer subscribers are more likely to maintain high NRR, but all SaaS companies grow at similar rates despite their subscriber size.  </p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg" width="1247" height="681" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:681,&quot;width&quot;:1247,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:74284,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F22325510-f8b7-4dfb-b668-a9c358c801e2_1247x681.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><blockquote><h4><em><strong>‚úàÔ∏è KEY TAKEAWAYS</strong></em></h4><p><em>The SaaS landscape has shifted from hyper-growth to sustainable, expansion-focused growth, with NRR becoming a more challenging metric as companies scale. Strong retention strategies are crucial to thriving in this new normal.</em></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h2>Founder Titles Change Over Time</h2><p>A recent <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/ilyavcandpe_stanford-stanfordgsb-venturecapital-activity-7250158206482558976-tnXy?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=member_desktop">study</a> by Ilya Strebulaev of 1,110 US-based VC-backed unicorns reveals that while CEO remains the dominant title for founders, many hold roles you might not expect. From more traditional leadership positions to quirky titles, the data showcases the diversity of founder roles in today‚Äôs unicorn startups.</p><ul><li><p><strong>CEO leads the pack:</strong> 34% of unicorn founders are CEOs, followed by 16% who serve as Chairman or VP.</p></li><li><p><strong>CTO and President are strong</strong>: 13% of founders are CTOs, while 12% hold the President role.</p></li><li><p><strong>Rare C-suite titles</strong>: Only 4% of unicorn founders serve as COO, and less than 2% hold other C-suite roles like CFO, CMO, or Chief Strategy Officer.</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg" width="720" height="404.5054945054945" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:818,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:720,&quot;bytes&quot;:115337,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0917b028-df7d-4fad-a10c-279d70abed8a_1690x950.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><blockquote><h4><em><strong>‚úàÔ∏è KEY TAKEAWAYS</strong></em></h4><p><em>While many founders assume CEO roles, the variety of titles, even unconventional ones, speaks to the flexible, often innovative nature of startup leadership.</em></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif" width="480" height="270" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:270,&quot;width&quot;:480,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Ball Share GIF by StickerGiant&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Ball Share GIF by StickerGiant&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Ball Share GIF by StickerGiant" title="Ball Share GIF by StickerGiant" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_lossy/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd775c953-c12b-4d00-8d3f-8f13d50677fd_480x270.gif 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><div class="captioned-button-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.datadrivenvc.io/p/data-driven-vc-24-an-emerging-vcs?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&amp;token=eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjo4ODkwMTQ1LCJwb3N0X2lkIjoxMDQ0ODMzOTksImlhdCI6MTY3NzUxODk0MSwiZXhwIjoxNjgwMTEwOTQxLCJpc3MiOiJwdWItMTA4MzIxMSIsInN1YiI6InBvc3QtcmVhY3Rpb24ifQ.821GUT1ZoRJ4h6lZsu-O08lBC1hA4d44LPvGHFYKavg&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;}" data-component-name="CaptionedButtonToDOM"><div class="preamble"><p class="cta-caption">Share this article with others who might benefit.</p></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/p/time-between-funding-rounds-startup?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/p/time-between-funding-rounds-startup?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p></div><div><hr></div><h2>Tech Talent Trends</h2><p>We just found a nugget: SignalFire‚Äôs 2023 Talent <a href="https://www.signalfire.com/blog/state-of-talent-tech-trends">Report</a> digs into shifts in tech employment trends, showing how layoffs, AI growth, and changing work locations are shaping the tech workforce. As Silicon Valley faces relocation challenges, new tech hubs like Austin and NYC are emerging. Meanwhile, Gen Z‚Äôs career dynamics are reshaping expectations for promotions and job stability.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Austin grows the most:</strong> Austin's tech talent surged 44%, the highest among VC-backed companies, while big tech growth in Seattle hit 20%.</p></li><li><p><strong>Gen Z job-hopping</strong>: Gen Z changed jobs twice as often as Gen X, impacting their upward mobility and reluctance to enter management roles.</p></li><li><p><strong>AI hires shift</strong>: Less than half of new AI recruits now have graduate degrees, with AI startups driving talent growth over traditional academic routes.</p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp" width="656" height="475.7802197802198" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1056,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:656,&quot;bytes&quot;:127132,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/webp&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2f6e016-2a24-4a5a-b826-a077bc213ead_1920x1392.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><blockquote><h4><em><strong>‚úàÔ∏è KEY TAKEAWAYS</strong></em></h4><p><em>Tech is moving geographically, generational trends are reshaping promotions, and AI‚Äôs growth is redefining talent qualifications. Adaptability is key for staying competitive in the changing landscape.</em></p></blockquote><div><hr></div><h2>The Struggles of Mid-Market SaaS Deals  </h2><p>A great new <a href="https://www.mostlymetrics.com/p/the-messy-middle">breakdown</a> by our friend CJ at Mostly Metrics reveals that mid-sized SaaS deals, especially those between $50K and $100K, are facing increased scrutiny as companies look to cut budgets. CFOs are more likely to target these deals for consolidation, trimming non-essential software while holding on to mission-critical systems like AWS or NetSuite. </p><ul><li><p><strong>Implementation inertia:</strong> Large software implementations create sunk costs that discourage removal.  </p></li><li><p><strong>Vendor consolidation:</strong> Companies are bundling tools to save, cutting standalone products.  </p></li><li><p><strong>Mid-market vulnerability:</strong> $50K‚Äì$100K tools are more likely to be eliminated than lower-cost or critical systems.  </p></li></ul><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg" width="942" height="560" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:560,&quot;width&quot;:942,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:88374,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fbc8ec330-e2c5-464f-8100-4fb81c169469_942x560.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,