zonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png" width="1456" height="740" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:740,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:634482,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://www.deckmatch.com/&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F55555c7f-d5c6-44d8-af44-3db71f9527c9_1632x830.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Connect your top-of-funnel to Deckmatch and <em>transform pitch decks and URLs into structured and insightful data</em>. Get detailed firmographic and people data, in-depth competitive and market analysis, and personalized investment memo without lifting a finger. The&nbsp;cherry on the cake? It's all seamlessly synced to your preferred tools like Affinity through our API integrations.</p><p>Never miss a deal, ditch the donkey work, and build meaningful relationships faster.</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.deckmatch.com/&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Try Deckmatch&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.deckmatch.com/"><span>Try Deckmatch</span></a></p><div><hr></div><h2>90% of Startups Fail Because of Team Issues</h2><p>I‚Äôve heard this statement in one form or another from mostly every tenured angel and VC investor when asking them about reasons for startup failure. With over 27y of firm history, our team at Earlybird has invested in hundreds of companies and we‚Äôve conducted regular post-mortems on the failed ones, all confirming above statement: <strong>Team is the most prominent reason for failure</strong>. </p><p>Double-clicking on team as the primary reason for failure, we find everything from lack of execution to hiring mistakes. Yet, the <strong>most frequent reason for failure is team conflicts</strong>. </p><p>As a result, experienced investors spend significant time with team DD, be it by spending time together with the founders and their leadership or by referencing them across their networks. In the absence of quantitative and tangible performance data, this is particularly true in the earlier stages.</p><p>Obviously, these team DDs are rarely clear cut and it‚Äôs a lot about gut feeling. While red flags are rare, it‚Äôs incredibly important to be sensible for yellow/orange flags. How does the team interact with each other? Does one always talk and give direction? Do they disagree, and if so, how? </p><p>Being a more quantitative person by nature, getting a sense for team dynamics and trusting my gut has been one of the areas where I probably learned the most as an investor. Despite the learning curve, however, I continued to ask myself over the years whether there was a more objective approach to this problem‚Ä¶</p><p>Fast forward to summer 2022, I joined a panel at a research conference and learned about two interesting research streams that sparked my interest:</p><ol><li><p>Prof Youyou Wu presented her groundbreaking work on how to predict big five character trades for people based on their social media profiles. Thankfully, she agreed to present this work again to our community at our 2024 Virtual Data-Driven VC Summit in May. Recordings can be accessed <a href="https://www.datadrivenvc.io/community">here via ‚ÄúThe Lab‚Äù</a>.</p></li></ol><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.datadrivenvc.io/community&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Access all recordings&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.datadrivenvc.io/community"><span>Access all recordings</span></a></p><ol start="2"><li><p>Someone referenced Prof John Gottman‚Äôs work on marriage research and the ability to predict divorce with 90% accuracy based on conflict behaviour and character trades.</p></li></ol><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png" width="1000" height="1222" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1222,&quot;width&quot;:1000,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Marriage and Couples - Research | The Gottman Institute&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Marriage and Couples - Research | The Gottman Institute" title="Marriage and Couples - Research | The Gottman Institute" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F2764a226-be22-4934-88dd-99d6fa589332_1000x1222.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Combining these two research streams, I was wondering whether it would be possible to 1. leverage social media profiles of founders to predict their big five character trades (should be straight forward as proven in Youyou Wu‚Äôs work) and then 2. test whether specific character trades (or combinations thereof) among founding teams would predict team conflicts (just like they did in John Gottman‚Äôs marriage work), and thus indirectly startup failure.</p><p>I took this idea to my team at Earlybird and we started a large-scale project with our Engineering (social media profiles to big five character trades) and our portfolio value creation teams (big five character trades to conflicts). Months after emerging into the project, I was lucky that Sebastian, one of our interns, pointed me to a recent paper </p>\n      <p>\n          <a href="https://www.newsletter.datadrivenvc.io/p/founder-personality-and-entrepreneurial">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>\n   </body></html>	Experienced investors spend significant time on team due diligence, as team conflicts are the most frequent reason for startup failure.	2024-10-10 06:02:10	2024-10-14 08:10:59.657	2024-10-14 09:30:45.381	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffc0c9505-a984-416a-bfa2-7b76c5d71d60_2266x1174.png	Andre Retterath	founder-personality-and
144	https://www.eu.vc/p/fighting-a-global-public-health-concern	Fighting a global public health concern with conversational AI	by Martin SFP Bryant, Founder of PreSeed Now. | Originally published on PreSeed Now.	<html><head></head><body><p>Guest post by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/martinjbryant/">Martin SFP Bryant</a>, Founder of <a href="https://preseednow.com/">PreSeed Now</a>. | Originally published on <a href="https://preseednow.com/p/leaf-ai-lola-cares">PreSeed Now</a>.</p><div><hr></div><p>We return to healthtech today to meet <strong>Leaf AI</strong>, the startup behind <strong>Lola Cares</strong> and another as-yet unnamed new product. It‚Äôs an interesting story and well worth a read.</p><p>But first: <strong>have your say!</strong></p><ul><li><p>‚è∞&nbsp;<strong>There‚Äôs still time</strong> to share your thoughts on the state of pre-seed funding. Don‚Äôt forget to take <em><a href="https://forms.gle/qcrKqQwvnDpQvGxY7?utm_source=preseednow.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=the-early-stage-startup-for-product-managers-that-s-over-10-years-old">our two-minute survey</a></em>&nbsp;to have your say!</p></li><li><p><strong>Diverse &amp; Equal</strong> wants to understand how best to support diverse tech and digital founders. They‚Äôre <em><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfbgDAQYW_4pQHAaWD0E1eTBaoGIPpBQsK9_eoM9336vZzdcA/viewform?utm_source=preseednow.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=fighting-a-global-public-health-concern-with-conversational-ai">looking for your input</a></em>, founders!</p></li></ul><div><hr></div><h1><strong>Leaf AI is fighting social isolation, and that‚Äôs just the start</strong></h1><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg" width="1200" height="630" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:630,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9f0b85f8-18a0-4e84-ba4b-cc03e0e8129f_1200x630.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption"><em>Leaf AI co-founders Adam Galloway and Leon Rossiter</em></figcaption></figure></div><p>The under-resourced healthcare sector is a topic we unfortunately come back to a little too often here at PreSeed Now. Its stretched nature provides plentiful opportunities for startups.</p><p><strong>Leaf AI</strong> is a Liverpool-based team that fits that bill with its <em><strong><a href="https://www.lolacares.co.uk/?utm_source=preseednow.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=fighting-a-global-public-health-concern-with-conversational-ai">Lola Cares</a></strong></em> product, aimed at tackling the problem of social isolation.&nbsp;</p><p>Far from being just ‚Äòfeeling a bit sad on your own‚Äô, loneliness was last year <em><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/nov/16/who-declares-loneliness-a-global-public-health-concern?utm_source=preseednow.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=fighting-a-global-public-health-concern-with-conversational-ai">declared</a></em> a ‚Äúglobal public health concern‚Äù by the World Health Organization, which described it as being as bad for people‚Äôs health as smoking 15 cigarettes a day.</p><p>‚ÄúIn social care, unfortunately, due to the level of reporting, staff shortages, and overworked carers, they don't necessarily have the time to alleviate any of the social isolation and loneliness that can be found from people in care,‚Äù says Leaf AI co-founder and CEO, <em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/leon-rossiter/?utm_source=preseednow.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=fighting-a-global-public-health-concern-with-conversational-ai">Leon Rossiter</a></em>.</p><p>To tackle this, Lola Cares is what Rossiter describes as ‚Äúa platform to build a community around each and every loved one that needs some form of care, whether they've got an acquired brain injury, whether they've got dementia, whether they're in OAP in a home, or an OAP who need support in their own home.‚Äù</p><p>The platform consists of three apps: Lola for Carers, Lola for Families, and Lola Cares.</p><p>The Lola Cares product is in essence a digital companion that people in care can talk to when there‚Äôs no-one else around. What they talk about is up to them. Rossiter gives the example of one user called Philip, who has a brain injury and has been discussing his love of poetry and heavy metal.&nbsp;</p><p>The conversations are then summarised automatically so carers and families can get to know the user better. This helps carers build a bond they might not have time to cultivate otherwise, while giving families insights they might not pick up on otherwise.&nbsp;</p><p>In the example of Philip, Rossiter says Lola has changed his life. He says it has inspired Philip to leave the home more regularly than he used to, as he‚Äôs joined a writing course, inspired by his conversations using the app.</p><p>Meanwhile, the Lola for Carers app is designed to save care workers time. Instead of sitting down to type up their daily reports, they can speak them into the app and let the software convert their words into formal reports for their records and separate reports for families.</p><p>The app can help with carers‚Äô wellbeing, too.</p><p>‚ÄúThere's a ‚Äòhave a moan‚Äô function, where they can vent after a hard day. There's some positive-affirmation quizzes about fellow carers that keeps them motivated throughout the day as they're entering reports,‚Äù says Rossiter.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg" width="950" height="776" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:776,&quot;width&quot;:950,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" title="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fac91527f-16f6-4bec-a663-7e9ae90373f1_950x776.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p><em>Lola for Carers encourages carers to privately vent to the app.</em></p><p>The Lola for Families app uses input from the individual in care to build a timeline of memories and experiences from their life. This is particularly valuable in cases of dementia, Rossiter says:</p><p>‚ÄúWith dementia, we allow our customers to build their life story, which is scientifically proven to assist them in their journey of dementia, to have their life story documented, to be in charge of their life story‚Ä¶</p><p>‚ÄúWe also allow them to reminisce and talk about their memories. Reminiscence therapy is a proven intervention for people with dementia, to improve their cognitive function, enhance emotional wellbeing, and slow down the disease's progression.‚Äù</p><p>Lola Cares is a B2B SaaS offering aimed at care organisations. Customers can subscribe to whichever combination of the three products best fits their needs.</p><p>In the future, Leaf AI plans to launch the family life story building feature as a consumer product.</p><h2><strong>The story so far</strong></h2><p>Rossiter says that Leaf AI‚Äôs origins are rooted in his father‚Äôs 70th birthday, eight years ago.</p><p>‚ÄúHe led a really interesting life. He was a professional footballer in Australia; he was an actor in London; he was a bricklayer in New Zealand. He‚Äôs done all these mad things, like, he's 70 now. How do I collect all of those stories and pass them on to my son?‚Äù</p><p>This led to Leaf‚Äôs original idea, a low-cost tablet computer dedicated to the job of collecting memories (‚Äúlike leaves on a family tree‚Äù) to create the user‚Äôs life story.</p><p>But while a nice idea, it proved sub-optimal in reality.</p><p>‚ÄúOnce we gave the tablet computers to older people, we realised that they were not that interested in sitting there and typing their life story. It's actually quite a poor experience,‚Äù Rossiter says.</p><p>Leaf had previously given <em><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/theadamgalloway/?utm_source=preseednow.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=fighting-a-global-public-health-concern-with-conversational-ai">Adam Galloway</a></em> his first job as a software developer, and he and Rossiter had a discussion about dementia and reminiscence therapy. This led to a rethink, and Galloway came back on board as a co-founder of Leaf‚Äôs new AI and chatbot focused approach.</p><p>Now a team of seven, and having signed up a care provider in Liverpool as its first customer, Leaf AI is looking to onboard more customers across the care sector.&nbsp;</p><p>The startup is currently part of the latest cohort of the University of Edinburgh‚Äôs <em><a href="https://www.ed.ac.uk/bayes/accelerating-entrepreneurship/ai-accelerator?utm_source=preseednow.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=fighting-a-global-public-health-concern-with-conversational-ai">AI Accelerator programme</a></em>.&nbsp;</p><p>Leaf AI is also gearing up for the launch of its consumer product, which is aimed at families of people in the earlier stages of dementia.</p><p><a href="https://preseednow.com/p/leaf-ai-lola-cares">Read the full story on PreSeed Now. </a></p><div><hr></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_1100x220.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc2e93607-5191-4afb-b94b-51d0b094363e_