CnlvuJNfcWIIZ0rHseGKFjnGB_l-rnSVvL2fFtOabsEKiicZuoFx0YJwwwLQjyQsmFDNCcy6FMlTSmSljlHIc1g1mLWm7Q7F8LpNief-KjLaxtg7hNw0lk9SWD-uHxfc6kBz-3fvVJvlrEq9JvJ7noWstEN9w40nvMIkXuca6hJLzOFP_XvCE9cD4b3-N9UgBeirnkqIX0szOkuov6DWFBJNiOOgdSBtrLBnS6eHoe8H2ya1XhEz6T4GjYf17JqTRwjpFbi_-BAAA__-R9HXH">Broadhaven Ventures</a>. | Originally published on <a href="https://altgoesmainstream.substack.com/p/cantilever-groups-todd-owens-the">Alt Goes Mainstream</a>.</p><p><strong>Why it matters: </strong>This episode unpacks GP stakes investing, spotlighting a middle-market opportunity many overlook. Todd Owens of Cantilever Group discusses how GP stakes provide capital for growth, founder liquidity, and generational transitions‚Äîcritical as alternative asset managers evolve.  </p><p>GP stakes allow exposure to expanding private markets AUM, making them an intriguing option for investors aiming to tap into alternative asset growth without directly managing funds.</p><p><a href="https://www.eu.vc/p/alt-goes-mainstream-ep-105-cantilever">Listen to the podcast episode here.</a></p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ec2817e-7d9e-456b-8456-0ccf22a1726c_700x40.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ec2817e-7d9e-456b-8456-0ccf22a1726c_700x40.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0ec2817e-7d9e-456b-8456-0ccf22a1726c_700x40.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fs