ke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p></p></li><li><p><strong>Imagine </strong>providing your LPs with innovative liquidity solutions, enabling you to relieve the pain of illiquidity.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Imagine </strong>leveraging an intuitive platform that automates routine processes like capital calls, transfers, reporting, and capital management, allowing you to dedicate more time to creating value for your investors.<strong><br></strong></p></li></ul><p>The future of private market investing is not only more efficient but also more transparent, inclusive, and data-driven. This is the vision we are building at Allocate‚Äîcreating a platform that transforms how investors and fund managers interact with private markets, making it more accessible, efficient, and intelligent through the power of data and purpose built software.</p><p>Want to learn more?<a href="https://app.allocate.co/apply"> Click here to get in touch with u</a>s (or email me directly at Samir@allocate.co). </p></body></html>	The private markets have grown significantly, but the current system is inefficient and lacks transparency. Allocate aims to modernize the private market experience through technology, providing personalized investment opportunities, seamless investing, and real-time portfolio management for investors.	2024-10-02 21:11:31	2024-10-14 08:17:11.557	2024-10-14 09:20:44.198	{vc}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1e1a411d-c1c8-4efc-a26e-0275d9ef60d1_2254x983.png	Samir Kaji	private-market-investing-is
138	https://akashbajwa.substack.com/p/inference-time-scaling-laws	Inference Time Scaling Laws 	AI Megacycle Of System 1 And System 2 Applications	<html><head></head><body><p><em>üëã Hey friends, I‚Äôm <strong><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/akashbajwa/">Akash</a>! </strong>Software Synthesis is where I connect the dots on AI, software and company building strategy. You can reach me at<strong> akash@earlybird.com</strong>!</em></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://akashbajwa.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://akashbajwa.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><div><hr></div><p>Pre-training scaling laws may soon hit a data wall, but OpenAI‚Äôs o1 model has revealed an entirely new scaling law: <strong>inference time scaling</strong>. </p><div><hr></div><p>Until very recently, most of the focus in LLM scaling was on pre-training. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://x.com/draecomino/status/1834657347127722191" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png" width="491" height="193" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:193,&quot;width&quot;:491,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:38283,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://x.com/draecomino/status/1834657347127722191&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F9d5a758d-6e84-4c4b-a8d0-97cb1b4e6eb2_491x193.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>With compute capacity used for training doubling every 6 months for the last 14 years.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://epochai.org/data/notable-ai-models" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png" width="894" height="460" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:460,&quot;width&quot;:894,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:115463,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://epochai.org/data/notable-ai-models&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F731d9fcd-7720-4c59-8e29-f4bab2b0665e_894x460.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: Epoch AI</figcaption></figure></div><p>Despite the <a href="https://x.com/ecommerceshares/status/1834282317957005324">hundreds of billions of capex</a> going into AI data centres, we‚Äôre likely to hit a data wall in 2027/28. </p><blockquote><p><em>There‚Äôs this big debate in the AI field about what are the rate-limiters on progress, and the scaling purists think we need more scale, more compute. There are people who believe we need algorithmic breakthroughs, and so we are AI researcher limited, and then there are folks who believe we‚Äôre hitting a data wall, and what we‚Äôre actually gated on is high-quality data and maybe labeled data, maybe raw data, maybe video can provide it.</em></p><p><em><strong><a href="https://stratechery.com/2024/an-interview-with-daniel-gross-and-nat-friedman-about-apple-and-ai/">Nat Friedman</a></strong></em></p></blockquote><p>Short of breakthroughs in architectures, current progress can only be extrapolated for a few more years (even if there would be transformative value in just realising the latent capabilities of frontier models).</p><p>That‚Äôs why inference-time scaling laws matter.</p><p>o1 reallocates compute from pre-training to inference time, allowing it to ‚Äòthink‚Äô and reason about problems for longer.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://x.com/DrJimFan/status/1834279865933332752" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg" width="680" height="382" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:382,&quot;width&quot;:680,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Image&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://x.com/DrJimFan/status/1834279865933332752&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Image" title="Image" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: Jim Fan</figcaption></figure></div><blockquote><p><em>Just like the scaling law for training, this seems to have no limit, but also like the scaling law for training, it is exponential, so to continue to improve outputs, you need to let the AI ‚Äúthink‚Äù for ever longer periods of time. It makes the fictional computer in The Hitchhikers Guide to the Galaxy, which needed 7.5 million years to figure out the ultimate answer to the ultimate question, feel more prophetic than a science fiction joke. We are in the early days of the ‚Äúthinking‚Äù scaling law, but it shows a lot of promise for the future.</em></p><p><em><span class="mention-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Ethan Mollick&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:846835,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;user&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:null,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7c05cdbc-40fd-459b-915d-f8bc8ac8bf01_3509x5263.jpeg&quot;,&quot;uuid&quot;:&quot;3484db88-641c-483b-9742-4eb2bbfebab0&quot;}" data-component-name="MentionToDOM"></span></em> </p></blockquote><p>One way to taxonomise AI capabilities and enterprise use cases is System 1 vs System 2. </p><blockquote><p><em>‚ÄòOne way to think about reasoning is there are some problems that benefit from being able to think about it for longer. You know, there‚Äôs this classic notion of System 1 versus System 2 thinking in humans. System 1 is the more automatic, instinctive response and <strong>System 2 is the slower, more process-driven response</strong>.‚Äô</em></p><p><em><a href="https://www.sequoiacap.com/podcast/training-data-noam-brown/">Noam Brown</a></em></p></blockquote><p>Much of AI‚Äôs promise of ‚Äòselling work‚Äô relies on 'agentic‚Äô capabilities like reflection, intelligent function calling, planning. Effectively, reasoning. </p><p>Chain of thought and reflection tokens which explicitly instruct a model to follow certain steps in the execution of a task, reflect on the outputs of each step before moving on to the next, and use the right tools to fetch context/knowledge, are how developers have derived agentic capabilities from existing frontier models.</p><p>In terms of purely focusing on inference scaling, we‚Äôre probably in the GPT-1 era of capabilities.</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://scale.com/leaderboard" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png" width="607" height="597" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:597,&quot;width&quot;:607,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:63143,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://scale.com/leaderboard&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F781818c8-9df6-4bc7-9b58-6514a8461c2a_607x597.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a></figure></div><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp" width="1456" height="818" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:818,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;The image shows two scatter plots comparing \\&quot;o1 AIME accuracy\\&quot; during training and at test time. Both charts have \\&quot;pass@1 accuracy\\&quot; on the y-axis and compute (log scale) on the x-axis. The dots indicate increasing accuracy with more compute time.&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="The image shows two scatter plots comparing &quot;o1 AIME accuracy&quot; during training and at test time. Both charts have &quot;pass@1 accuracy&quot; on the y-axis and compute (log scale) on the x-axis. The dots indicate increasing accuracy with more compute time." title="The image shows two scatter plots comparing &quot;o1 AIME accuracy&quot; during training and at test time. Both charts have &quot;pass@1 accuracy&quot; on the y-axis and compute (log scale) on the x-axis. The dots indicate increasing accuracy with more compute time." srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb9d47016-da1b-4152-a560-d272e71e30da_1980x1113.webp 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: OpenAI</figcaption></figure></div><blockquote><p><em>The thing that remains to be solved is general domain long horizon reliability. And I think you need inference time compute, test time compute, for that. So you‚Äôd want‚Äîwhen you try to prove a new theorem in math, or when you‚Äôre writing a large software program, or when you‚Äôre writing an essay of reasonable complexity, you usually wouldn‚Äôt write it token by token. </em></p><p><em>You‚Äôd want to think quite hard about some of those tokens. And finding ways to spend not 1X or 2x or 10X, but a <strong>1,000,000X the resources on that token in a productive way</strong>, I think, is really important. That is probably the last big problem.</em></p><p><em><a href="https://www.sequoiacap.com/podcast/training-data-eric-steinberger/">Eric Steinberger</a></em></p></blockquote><p>Even if we scale up inference time compute by the orders of magnitude Eric is implying, it‚Äôd still be much cheaper than human workers, as <a href="https://stratechery.com/2024/enterprise-philosophy-and-the-first-wave-of-ai/">Ben Thompson pointed out</a>:</p><blockquote><p><em>This second image is a potential problem in a Copilot paradigm: sure, a smarter model potentially makes your employees more productive, but those increases in productivity have to be balanced by both greater inference costs and more time spent waiting for the model (o1 is significantly slower than a model like 4o). However, the agent equation, where you are talking about replacing a worker, is dramatically different: there the cost umbrella is absolutely massive, because even the most expensive model is a <strong>lot cheaper, above-and-beyond the other benefits like always being available and being scalable in number</strong>.</em></p></blockquote><p>There‚Äôs some <a href="https://x.com/_philschmid/status/1842846050320544016">early evidence</a> that applying the right RL + CoT techniques can yield similar levels of performance from other frontier models that haven‚Äôt fully exploited inference time scaling, likely owing to some hidden chain of thought tokens. In any case, the other labs are undoubtedly investing these new scaling laws and repurposing their compute. </p><p>As the other labs collectively channel their resources towards inference time scaling, we‚Äôll see use cases and capabilities flourish. The early high-ROI use cases of code generation and customer service will benefit from system 2 reasoning, becoming capable of replacing more experienced workers. Inference time scaling will also unlock novel system 2 functions like financial planning and analysis, corporate development, and strategy. </p><p>The most exciting conclusion is how multiple <a href="https://www.usv.com/writing/2018/10/the-myth-of-the-infrastructure-phase/">app &lt;&gt; infrastructure cycles</a> are combining into an AI megacycle, just as previous technology waves were stacked on top of each other to create de novo products and experiences. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://blog.eladgil.com/p/megacycles-in-tech-crypto" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png" width="400" height="229" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/cce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:229,&quot;width&quot;:400,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://blog.eladgil.com/p/megacycles-in-tech-crypto&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcce20225-e41a-4aa0-9181-961629d99517_400x229.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></a><figcaption class="image-caption">Source: Elad Gil</figcaption></figure></div><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://akashbajwa.substack.com/p/inference-time-scaling-laws?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://akashbajwa.substack.com/p/inference-time-scaling-laws?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://akashbajwa.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://akashbajwa.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://akashbajwa.substack.com/?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share Software Synthesis&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://akashbajwa.substack.com/?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=share&amp;action=share"><span>Share Software Synthesis</span></a></p><p><em>Thank you for reading. If you liked this piece, please share it with your friends, colleagues, and anyone that wants to get smarter on startup strategy. Subscribe and find me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/akashbajwa/">LinkedIn</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/AkashBajwa96">Twitter</a>.</em></p><p></p><p></p></body></html>	A newsletter on AI, software, and company building strategy. How pre-training scaling laws may soon hit a data wall.	2024-10-07 06:03:28	2024-10-14 08:16:56.259	2024-10-14 09:20:44.198	{vc,ai}	https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45d2d226-2f2a-4bd5-bf2d-6e12b6f2256c_680x382.jpeg	Akash Bajwa	inference-time-scaling
136	https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/p/how-to-announce-your-fundraise	How to Announce Your Fundraise	And the most common mistake I see with announcements	<html><head></head><body><p>Hey y‚Äôall ‚Äî fundraising is one thing, announcing your fundraise is another.</p><p>After the money‚Äôs been wired, you probably just want to tell everyone about it. It‚Äôs an exciting thing.</p><p>But there are a lot of reasons to be more strategic about your announcement, and a lot of factors you should consider to shape how, where, and when to announce it.</p><p>It‚Äôs a moment of organic gravity for your startup, product, and brand ‚Äî don‚Äôt treat it as an afterthought.</p><p>When we raised our Series A from a16z we didn‚Äôt do everything perfectly with our announcement, but we did enough right to make it a trajectory-changing event for the company.</p><p>This week I‚Äôm breaking down:</p><ul><li><p>How to time your announcement</p></li><li><p>How to drive attention to your announcement</p></li><li><p>Where to announce</p></li><li><p>What to include</p></li><li><p>The most common mistake I see</p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://thefoundingjourney.substack.com/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a></p></li></ul><div><hr></div><p>This is October‚Äôs ‚ú®<strong> free </strong>‚ú® deep dive, and you can read the full post below. <a href="https://upgrade.foundingjourney.com">Become a member</a> to get a new one in full each week.</p><h2><strong>How to Announce Your Fundraise</strong></h2><h3><strong>Timing Your Announcement</strong></h3><p>You can set one of two primary goals for announcing a fundraise:</p><ol><li><p>Accelerate the business (user growth, partnerships, and/or hiring)</p></li><li><p>Kick off your <em>next</em> round</p></li></ol><p>If you nail the execution of your announcement then investors are going to reach out either way, so here‚Äôs a simple framework to decide what your primary goal should be:</p><p>Ask yourself two questions:</p><ol><li><p>How much does the business need to grow more before raising more capital?</p></li><li><p>Do you need to accelerate growth to hit those numbers?</p></li></ol><p>If you need substantial growth, and need to accelerate to hit it or don‚Äôt have your growth channels fully figured out yet then it‚Äôs a good idea to announce sooner rather than later and leverage the momentum you receive from the raise.</p><p>If either of those things are <em>not</em> true, then you‚Äôre likely better off holding the fundraise in your back pocket until you‚Äôre ready to raise again.</p><p>There are other practical reasons to wait, too.</p><p>For example, if you close your round in November or December you‚Äôre likely better off waiting to announce til February (everyone else will be announcing in January, which makes it noisy for fundraising announcements).</p><h3><strong>Driving Attention</strong></h3><p>Legacy media no longer has a monopoly on driving attention.</p><p>In fact, even tech publications sort of begrudgingly cover fundraises these days ‚Äî if they do, it‚Äôs probably because the product fits some larger narrative they‚Äôre interested in.</p><p>The good news is you don‚Äôt need them, and you can nail your announcement solely with social media.</p><p>Here are some tips:</p><ol><li><p><strong>Announce in the morning ‚Üí</strong> There are two reasons for this. First, when people log on throughout the day the content that will be at the top of their feed will be what the algo thinks they‚Äôll be most likely to engage with, so getting engagement signals on your content before then increases the chances it will be shown. Second, after 12 hours or so your content will be relatively stale so you want those 12 hours to occur during the day, when most people are online. This is true no matter which social media platform you‚Äôre announcing on. The earlier, the better (I like 8:30am EST if you‚Äôre in the US, personally).</p></li><li><p><strong>Coordinate ahead of time ‚Üí </strong>Send an email to your entire contact list the day before letting them know you have a big announcement going live the following day, at a specific time, in a specific place (platform and account). Explicitly ask them to comment and repost on the announcement. Then, send another message <em>with the post‚Äôs URL as a link</em> immediately after it goes live.</p></li><li><p><strong>Direct all traffic to a single place ‚Üí</strong> The way to maximize reach on social media is immediate, relevant engagement on your post. This tells the algo that the post is interesting and should be shown to more people. If your email includes a link to your LinkedIn post, X post, website‚Äôs blog announcement, TechCrunch article, etc‚Ä¶ then you‚Äôre going to dilute the impact of each one and the combined impact of all of them will be far less than the impact of one would have been. The difference is huge. </p></li></ol><p>My creator partnership platform, <a href="https://megaphone.network">Megaphone</a>, can help with that last part btw. We let you get big creators involved and have helped tons of fundraising announcements at this point.</p><p>One founder even wrote me after their announcement saying it drove over 200 sales demos in the first couple hours.</p><h3><strong>Where to Announce</strong></h3><p>This one is simple:</p><p>Announce where it will have the biggest impact.</p><p>There are two factors:</p><ol><li><p>Where will you have the biggest megaphone (no pun intended)?</p></li><li><p>Where do the people you want to get in front of spend their time online?</p></li></ol><p>For example, if you‚Äôre optimizing for investor attention then you probably want to announce on X.</p><p>But if you have 10 followers on X and a million on TikTok, you might want to announce there instead.</p><p>You may also want to consider where you have the capability to create the most performant announcement post, but that‚Äôs secondary since you can always <a href="https://s665g04yp0s.typeform.com/to/rOXjvxHU">pay people to help create an engaging post</a>.</p><p>Your guiding principle here is that you want your announcement to enter the zeitgeist in some way. Figure out where you have the best shot of making that happen.</p><h3><strong>What to Include</strong></h3><p>There‚Äôs some basic info that every announcement should have:</p><ul><li><p><strong>How much you raised ‚Üí </strong>Bigger looks better but including the number makes it real, no matter what it is.</p></li><li><p><strong>What round it is ‚Üí</strong> This isn‚Äôt super important but does help people anchor their reaction.</p></li><li><p><strong>Who invested ‚Üí </strong>Lead with well known names, and don‚Äôt @ them ‚Äî just write their names (it‚Äôs more recognizable and the tag won‚Äôt matter since you‚Äôre alerting them via email anyway).</p></li><li><p><strong>Your company‚Äôs name ‚Üí</strong> You‚Äôd be surprised, I‚Äôve seen people forget this.</p></li><li><p><strong>Your one-liner ‚Üí</strong> In a concise way, tell people what you actually do.</p></li><li><p><strong>More context ‚Üí</strong> You likely have more to say that will fit in your one-liner. That‚Äôs ok. If you‚Äôre announcing on X just don‚Äôt pack it all into the first tweet ‚Äî start a thread that‚Äôs well formatted for skimmability with generous whitespace.</p></li><li><p><strong>An image or video ‚Üí</strong> People are visual, and posts with an image or video get a boost by the algo too.</p></li><li><p><strong>Somewhere to go ‚Üí </strong>You want to drive this traffic somewhere. Ideally you can capture their emails.</p></li></ul><p>Not everyone has an AI video model to launch at the same time as their fundraise announcement, but I‚Äôm including this as an example of one of the better announcements I‚Äôve seen in the last year:</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png" width="478" height="601.6206896551724" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:438,&quot;width&quot;:348,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:478,&quot;bytes&quot;:81413,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04968804-1462-4cb7-a8bb-6037617d460a_348x438.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>This violates the link-in-first-post rule, but the video had <em>so much</em> viral potential that it didn‚Äôt matter and likely worked in their favor (more impressions of the link = more link clicks).</p><p>And here was our Series A announcement (you can see we didn‚Äôt strictly follow the one-piece-of-content rule but it did well regardless, since we had a lot of hype at the time and did a good job driving attention to it):</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png" width="480" height="583.448275862069" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/d677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:423,&quot;width&quot;:348,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:480,&quot;bytes&quot;:89521,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd677712f-4455-494d-8642-1c3d7fda5dc2_348x423.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></a></figure></div><p>One other point here ‚Äî quality matters.</p><p>It‚Äôs worth announcing on your terms, once you have the post exactly how you want it since this will be your first impression to thousands of people.</p><h3><strong>The Most Common Mistake</strong></h3><p>Too often the main announcement post doesn‚Äôt say what the company actually does.</p><p>It might have big name investors and maybe even a concise, interesting backstory but 90%+ of the people who see the post are not going to click through to read all of it, or the entire thread, or watch the entire video.</p><p>I don‚Äôt mean to pick on anyone specific, but these are just some examples I saw recently of what is a much more common problem. I‚Äôm including them because they managed to do well despite making this mistake (not everyone is so lucky):</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2 is-viewable-imag" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2167129-6c78-4e6b-b323-f119f16207ff_349x510.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2167129-6c78-4e6b-b323-f119f16207ff_349x510.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2167129-6c78-4e6b-b323-f119f16207ff_349x510.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2167129-6c78-4e6b-b323-f119f16207ff_349x510.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2167129-6c78-4e6b-b323-f119f16207ff_349x510.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fa2167129-6c78-4e6b-b323-f119f16207ff_349x510.png" width="473" height="691.2034383954154" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/a2